Great company if you still print at home to keep the costs down.

review_text: This was my 1st order from Swift Ink. Delivery was quick. When I installed the cartridge and started printing the print came out very light and parts of the letters were missing. I never had this problem with the original HP Cartridge. I had to change the printer setting to triple print every character (which uses a lot more ink) but then the print came out good. After I printed 5 pages I was able to lower the printer setting to just double print every character so the print would come out good on the paper (so parts of the letters were not missing).  After I printed 10 pages I was able to set the printer back to just single printing every character and the printed page looks OK now.  Maybe the replacement cartridge I got from Swift Ink just had a slow start but seems to be working OK right now.  If it works good for the next several months and I'm able to print another 500 to 700 pages that look good in the single print mode (which is how I always used the Original HP Cartridge from HP) then I will be very impressed with Swift Ink and will buy from them again and again.
product_name: Replacement for Hewlett Packard 51626A (HP 26 Black) Ink Cartridge

review_title: Would give you a 5 star because I know your cartridges are good, but I am SO disappointed
review_text:
Please Please either stop shipping via fedex or make FedEx accountable for the chronic delays in delivering to our community here, Wrangell Alaska. I STILL have not received the ink, which I really needed before the class I taught yesterday. FedEx sends all of our freight to their Anchorage hub which is farther away from us than Seattle. Then it sits there in Anchorage for anywhere from one to several days before they either hand it off to USPS in Anchorage or fly it back down to Aero Services in Ketchikan.  Either way our stuff then is further delayed until usps or aero finally sends it on to us. The worst part is that FedEx tracking will say that it was delivered to Wrangell when it is not, it is still in Anchorage. The post office clerks have the ability to confirm the freight location after FedEx gives them our freight in Anchorage.  I am just fed up with experiencing this FedEx disappointment over and over again. 
Lisa T

Mark from Swift Ink called me. I had been unable to follow the YouTube video using the instructions. However, Mark walked me through it and now everything is fine. I did have to remove and reinstall the printer to get it back online but now I am back in business. I printed the status report too and the new black cartridge I installed reports that I am good for 1600 pages. Thanks Mark. review_text:
Being a return customer, it was time for me to purchase inks for my Epson Workforce 3540. This order was MANDATORY!!! because I ran out of two of my color inks yellow and magenta. Obviously, I did not move quick enough because a family member took the initiative to order ink but not from Swift AND not tell me. You talk about a nightmare. My color jobs were streaked and had no ink patches in what should have been a full deep black image print, it was awful. I opened that printer and my mouth hit the floor. I removed that foreign ink cartridge out and shut the printer off. Put a sign on it DO NOT USE. I came online and show this family member SwiftInk. com letting them know your inks are the ONLY inks I use. I am so glad you had the inks in stock and I order 3 of each CMYK high capacity. I was so glad to see my mail person with that package in their hand. I replaced ALL the inks and started new. After flushing and nozzle checking and printer testing. My colors were finally back to good prints (a red rose with shadows should be just that not a watered down red that was muddy gray) I had to flush so much I know I will need a new magenta because for some odd reason that color had to be repeatedly tested because the messed up cartridge my family member bought had to be flushed.

Overall, I am so glad I have the best inkjet supplier for my Epson Workforce 3540. Your inks are as described on your site and are the best color match for me and my family's arts/crafts projects.

review_text:
Swift ink is a prayer answered. 

Recently my HP 8700 printer would not print indicating incompatible ink which made no sense because I've had that ink in my printer for months with no problems. After googling I found out that there was an update and I don't recall selecting yes possibly it was automatic.

I found some YouTube troubleshoots where I took out the black cartridge and replaced with an original empty cartridge, shut printer off, cleaned it out. .. yada. .. nothing worked. I was just about to be forced to purchase overpriced ink at office depot and then I saw a ad for Swift Ink. Once on there site I emailed my issue and received a prompt response. 

The rep indicated that their ink would work something about the chip will pass, I can't remember the technicalities, so I figured I'd purchase it was a lot (extremely) less than what HP and Office Depot was charging which should be against the law. 

Oh and I received 10% discount for 1st time order!

Swift ink even sent me a link to video to turn off automatic updates on my 8700 printer. 

And IT WORKED! I am back to printing which is important for this lady who has a home office! 

Abundant blessings to Swift Ink for not trying to over charge customers and for having great customer support may your company prosper EXCEEDINGLY in Jesus name!

review_text: Printer ink from the printer company just seems too expensive. I am happy to have found Swiftink which provides 'recycled' ink for a better price.  I find that the black and color Swiftink works fine for my Epson Expression Photo XP-950 printer.  I mostly print black and white text, sometimes color, rarely photographs.  I have found that the photos I print and put on the refrigerator eventually bleed and fade but that may be as much about the inexpensive photo paper I buy as much as the ink.  The cartridges last a reasonable amount of time and I have never found them to clog even though it may be as long as 3 months between uses of color ink.  Swiftink has an easy to use website and delivers reliably.  I recycle my cartridges for free at the local Best Buy store.  It would be nice to qualify for some type of rebate when I recycle cartridges not only for additional cost savings but also to encourage everyone to recycle plastic and create less waste.

review_text:
My Canon printer is new, and the Swift Ink was the very first time I had replaced the ink. Installation was a snap. I WAS disappointed with the first prints, because they were very pale. BUT I just thought it through, and figured the ink needed to be absorbed by the sponges in the new cartridges, so I kept tinkering with the print settings. I am currently using Epson Matte photo paper, and I tried setting the printer for different photo paper stock. When I chose Photo Glossy, and tinkered with other print settings, I was able to match the Canon ink prints EXACTLY. I print photos, and cannot wait to get my hands on some Ilford satin photo paper. A friend of mine printed out one of my photos on that stock (It's $70 for 100 sheets, NOT cheap). 
 
I had absolutely NO problem installing the cartridges; the colors are vivid; I see no difference, but you may have to adjust your print settings. I don't forsee any problems. Thanks. I saved a ton of money.

review_text: I have been ordering my ink for various printers for a while now. Some printer brands I won't mention have sensors that detect you are not using their branded ink. I just ignore their tactic and proceed with my Swift Ink. I print more documents that include graphics and the colors are true and rich. Also do my fair share of photo printing. Even though my printer is not specifically for photos, I get very good results suitable for framing, even in 8 X 10 size. I buy the larger cartridges and am satisfied completely with the number of copies I can get out of their cartridges. For their great prices compared to brand name cartridges, it's a winning product at a huge savings. My current Epson prints the best quality pictures of all the brands of printers I've had. Don't know why, but very happy with the Swift Ink replacement ink and how it performs with this brand printer, which was a low-end affordable printer. I could not tell an iota difference in quality of print from the brand name ink that came with the new printer. I am now a dedicated purchaser of Swift Ink refurbished cartridges and wouldn't buy them anywhere else. Results far exceed what I've gotten from other sources of replacement ink, and I've had plenty of experience trying others over the years. Some were so bad in performance they went straight in the trash or wouldn't work at all with a brand fussy printer. I use my Swift Ink cartridges until they are empty, and they print true to color to the end.

review_text:
What drew me to these catridges was basically the huge cost savings over HP original costs. I was ready to throw out a good printer because the inks cost were so crazy. WalMart & Office Depot type costs were $105-115 for a five catridge set. Swift Ink remanufactured catridges were much cheaper. I think about $65.00 for two sets, 10 cartridges. 
Initially I thought I might have made a mistake. Be warned these cartridges leak & made a mess when you twist off the heads to install. Its a mess, spread out some newspapers & put on some latex gloves. Also when I did the first test print pages & did the head cleaning it was very disappointing. It took several tries & going to the deep clean to get a good test page. Also several of the catridges needed to be removed & reset because they didn't print any color. Simply removing & resetting cleared up this problem. Also I went back & did an additional print head cleaning & deep cleaning. This seemed to be a mistake. I started over. Reset the cartridges & did just the normal print head cleaning. 
It was quite a process but eventually I'm getting good test pages & the printer seems to be working fine. Also the cartridges display the ink remaining level even though you get a warning your not using HP approved cartridges. 
Barring these cartridges starting to mess up it looks like a good money saving alternative.
product_name: 10-Pack Compatible HP 564XL High Yield Ink Cartridges: 2 x Black/Photo/Cyan/Magenta/Yellow

review_text:
I've used a several dozen cartridges from Swift Ink and I am 100% satisfied. In the past I've used cartridges from several manufacturers and my experiences were awful (and that is being generous) to fatal to the health of the printer. The only reason I tried Swift was that Epson's cartridges are outrageously expensive. Short of giving up printing at home, I cannot afford to buy Epson cartridges. 
 
Swift's performance came as a very surprising. I've had only one cartridge malfunction. A simple Email resulted in the immediate shipment of a replacement. I also ran into a couple of cartridges that wouldn't work for more than a day. A call to Swift's customer support resulted in an email containing instructions for resetting the character counter inside the printer. 
 
The only negative to using any remanufactured cartridge or compatible cartridges is that all printer manufacturers do everything in their power to cause the printer to reject foreign ink. However, in the case of Swift Ink they stay on top of such issues and have a fix ready when you bump into new issues. 
 
Once you can use the Swift cartridges I recommend you ignore future firmware updates because they are the means by which the OEM printer manufacturer installs new ways to block using foreign cartridges. I think that updating the printer driver(s) is not a problem regarding the use of foreign cartridges. It is the firmware updates to be cautious of. 
 
Bottom line is I recommend Swift Ink every chance I get. I believe you will become a happy customer too.

review_text: I was highly skeptical of going third-party for ink for my new (to me) Brother MFC-J220 as plenty of horror stories abound on the internet, and Brother's official position is to not support the use of third-party ink (with the penalty of possible warranty voiding). However, I could not justify the expense of getting OEM Brother ink to fill my J220. After much searching online, I found that SwiftInk was generally highly regarded and recommended. I decided to take the plunge and ended up getting the 10-Pack (2C, 2Y, 2M, 4B) for less than 1/5 the cost of getting the same number of cartridges of OEM Brother InnoBella ink. Upon arrival, I was pleased to see that the packaging was incredibly minimal and was made out of post-consumer recycled paper products. The cartridges themselves were clear plastic, and filled up to the bleed hole on the top. They fit inside perfectly fine, and after an automatic clean cycle were good to go. Out of curiosity, I ran the two print quality tests and both checked out perfectly. The ink is fairly vibrant, moreso than the InnoBella (though not as vibrant as my HP's ink), lays down clean, and seems to work perfect. I've made three photo prints to date, and they've all come out wonderfully. The only possible complaint I have is that the B&W photo I printed on the Brother was mixed slightly odd (green cast), though that likely is a setting I need to tweak in the printer's driver control panel and not an issue with the ink itself. So, in summary, you're getting an environmentally conscious product for a budget price that also happens to be of incredibly high quality. What isn't to love?

review_text:
This is the 2nd time in 1 year I have ordered from them. Their ink is high quality and the cartridges fit my Brother Printer perfectly. The first time I ordered a year ago, I ordered the wrong ink. They immediately sent me the correct ink, my mistake completely, and they waited for me to return the box of ink. I did so immediately as well. This was a larger order that took me thru the year for my ink supply. Who does that today? Yes they even paid the shipping. I consulted with them about a new Brother printer, this year, and they said that printer would not take the same ink I was ordering. They quoted me a price for the new Brother printer INK and it was the same price. I asked them about the chips that companies (HP,Epson,Cannon,etc. ) are putting into their printers and on ink cartridges to tell if they are counterfeit (The Printer Companies word, not mine). He said that SwiftInk also has a chip on their cartridges now. So we can still buy a quality ink and not pay 4 times what it costs at the Big Box Stores. If I buy any piece of equipment and pay the MSRP, I feel I own it and should be able to put whatever paper, ink, light bulbs, gasoline, oil, tires, etc. that I can afford. These same manufacturers all have Foreign customer service technical support teams because it is cheaper than hiring in the USA. Well that is all I am doing too.
Order with confidence from SwiftInk. com you will not be disappointed. I ordered on Saturday morning and the box was delivered on Monday morning. They are in MD and I am in SC.  Amazing what Americans can do when they work Together!

review_text:
This is about the fourth or fifth time I've ordered these cartridges from Swift Ink.  That's a pretty good indication that I'm pleased with the product.  They aren't an exact match since Epson uses some sort of proprietary chip in their cartridges in order to make it difficult to use third party carts.  Epson cartridges will give you a warning that you're running low on ink.  These won't. At about a third of the price, I just make sure I always have a replacement ready.

This was the first time there was a delay in shipping.  They sent me an e-mail the day I ordered and let me know that they were out of stock and it would be about a week unitil new product was in.  They gave me some options.  I decided I could wait.  Three days after the stock was in I received my order.

I've tried other third party vendors with varying results.  These are the best I've found.

review_text:
The quality of the printouts with this ink has been excellent and I have no complaints at all. this is the first time I've used non OEM ink and I wish I'd started a long time ago. I have not printed any photos yet so I can't comment on that but I have no reason to believe it would be any different then ink. 

Two annoyances that don't merit losing a Star:
1. One cartridge (Officejet 8600 pro printer) took attempt to 'fit' - it was very tight. The others were fine. Once inserted it worked fine. 
2. The HP software will spam you with 'unofficial ink' warnings / borderline threats.  After a while they seem to go away. 

Bottom line - HP ink to refill printer  well over $100 - regular size on colors,  XL only on black.  All XL size ink from shiftink was around 1/4  or 1/5 of  with ink just as the HP cartels. 

Buy it -  you'll be happy - and if not there are numerous stories of their customer service going way above and beyond. Reminds me of what N**egg used  be like.

review_text:
My experience in graphic arts spans over 50 years. I have worked in the advertising, Screen printing, sign painting [with a brush], illustration, and sculpture. I turned on my first computer [goodwill] in January of 2013 and bought an Epson XP-300 printer [good product and service]. Bought my first digital camera [Dimage Z-20 at a yard sale], downloaded some free graphic software [komando. com] and began desktop publishing. After a few months learning how to avoid viruses and keep my nose clean on the net, I realized that ink was my largest expense.
   Swiftink was not a casual choice. Your company web page is clean, informative and user friendly. You offer [in my limited opinion] a broad and well stocked spectrum of products.

I decided to buy my ink through this site with the assumption that I would lose a couple dollars. I mean, and 750 page, XL black cartridge for $7.99? I figured, I'll give it a shot. Worst case scenario the cartridge doesn't fit, or the quality is terrible, and I lose $8. Boy was I wrong! 

First, it was cheap! I had never heard of generic equivalent ink before. I always thought you had to buy whatever your printers brand was. This price is almost to good to not at least give it a chance. 

Second, the service was incredible! Shipping was only like 2 or 3 bucks. I ordered on a Friday night, and my package was on the door step Monday when I got home from work. That's insane for shipping from any site. 

Third, the quality was amazing! I could not tell the difference between my name brand lexmark ink and this ink. I am officially a customer for life, and will tell all my friends and family about this site! Thanks so much!

review_text: I've been a Swift Ink customer for approximately two years. After buying my printer ink from Epson for several years, I decided that the cost of their product could not justified. I realize that the printer manufacturers have long used a business model where they give away their hardware at highly discounted prices and then make their profit (and lots of it) on the sale of their underfilled and overpriced ink cartridges. Well, after trying several other aftermarket printer ink suppliers (with very inconsistent results), I found Swiftink after doing another online search. Well, I can tell you that my experience with them has been nothing but positive. The prices of their ink cartridges are among the lowest I've found to date. The quality and performance is very high and very consistent. And, when they say that their cartridges are extra high capacity, they aren't kidding. It seems like they last forever. My ink expenditures have decreased by approximately 75% - this is not an exaggeration. In addition to all that I've just mentioned, Swiftink's order processing and shipping is outstanding. From the day that I place my order, the product will be in my mailbox in no more than three business days - for a flat rate cost of five dollars. With a qualifying order, the shipping is free. If you time your order properly, you can take advantage of their frequent 10% off sales. -- It's rather obvious that I'm an enthusiastic supporter of Swiftink.  I don't usually make testamonials like this, online or anywhere else. But, in this case, I'm willing to make an exception. I admire any business that has a great business model and knows how to put the customer first with providing an outstanding product, at a great price, and coupled with excellent customer service. Thanks. Swiftink, for a job well done!!  David R. - Minnesota, USA
